<subSubSection id="49D7162B9CA9350897E569D78FA299F6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="993EC31FEE423B34CA2EA14118DD5ED0" pageNumber="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="5BAD51323404196DE0DB4FEB346B5A4F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3582CA89-8236-4B5C-8098-37084743EA3D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carapidae" genus="Echiodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Echiodon Thompson 1837:55" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Echiodon Thompson</taxonomicName>
, 1837, comprises a group of 12 known species of pearlfishes found in a depth range of 18-2000m (Markle and Olney 1990; Williams and Machida 1992; Markle 1999). 
<taxonomicName id="7D9C56F6207FAE690FF897C39B81B61C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3582CA89-8236-4B5C-8098-37084743EA3D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carapidae" genus="Echiodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Echiodon Thompson 1837:55" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Echiodon</taxonomicName>
species are mainly deep-pelagic forms, although Markle (1999) suggested at least some may be facultative commensals (in benthic invertebrates like some other pearlfishes). Six of the 12 species of 
<taxonomicName id="845EEAAAA8544D8EC2F8BE947461B3E4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3582CA89-8236-4B5C-8098-37084743EA3D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carapidae" genus="Echiodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Echiodon Thompson 1837:55" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Echiodon</taxonomicName>
are found in temperate waters of the Southern Ocean. During cruise ICEFISH-04 (May to July 2004) across the South Atlantic on RVIB NATHANIEL B. PALMER, a specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="6AA366ADE52891B4DC33FBB395699B7C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3582CA89-8236-4B5C-8098-37084743EA3D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carapidae" genus="Echiodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Echiodon Thompson 1837:55" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Echiodon</taxonomicName>
was captured at the Tristan da Cunha Group. Originally thought by me to represent the circumglobal, austral 
<taxonomicName id="EF2966A8E905B0F506FD52FCE0FAC691" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2EE173D4-A7C6-4A62-B531-A7B18313F5AD" class="Actinopterygii" family="Carapidae" genus="Echiodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Echiodon cryomargarites Markle, Williams &amp; Olney 1983:647" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cryomargarites">E. cryomargarites Markle, Williams and Olney</taxonomicName>
, 1983, it possesses several characters in combination that reveal it is unnamed.
</paragraph>
